name: Rama Shinta Garden
address: Jl. Raya Denpasar - Gilimanuk No.9a, Mengwitani, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
This monument in mengwi
Display Rama and Shinta are characters from the ancient Indian epic, the Ramayana. Rama is the prince of Ayodhya and is known for his righteousness and bravery, while Shinta (also known as Sita) is his devoted wife. In some cultures, statues or sculptures of Rama and Shinta are created to depict their love story and the values they represent, such as loyalty, honor, and devotion. These statues can be found in temples, shrines, and other places of worship, serving as symbols of love, virtue, and the triumph of good over evil. They are often depicted together, showcasing their eternal bond and the enduring nature of their love story.
Been renovated and maintain by government.
